Undertaking to discharge arrears

The [applicant] / [respondent] shall discharge by [date], be solely responsible for and in any event indemnify the [respondent] / [applicant] against:

the arrears which have accrued in respect of the [policy] / [endowment policy] / [pension policy] with [company] numbered [policy number];

the arrears which have accrued in respect of the hire purchase agreement with [company] numbered [agreement number] in respect of the [car make and model] with registration number [reg. number];

the arrears which have accrued in respect of the loan agreement with [company] numbered [agreement number] in respect of [insert];

[etc].

Undertaking to use best endeavours to secure release from liabilities

The [applicant] / [respondent] shall use [his] / [her] best endeavours to obtain the consent of each creditor to release the [respondent] / [applicant] from any liability in respect of the following:

the hire purchase agreement with [company] numbered [agreement number] in respect of the [family car] / [car make and model] with registration number [reg. number];

the loan agreement with [company] numbered [agreement number] in respect of [insert];

[etc].

Undertaking to mitigate capital gains tax liability

The [applicant] / [respondent] shall take the following steps to mitigate any liability for capital gains tax or any other tax consequent upon the implementation of paragraph[s] [para number] of this order:

[set out as appropriate];

Undertaking to maintain medical insurance cover

The [respondent] / [applicant] shall maintain the existing medical insurance cover, including paying promptly any premiums due, with [company] or any successor company for:

the [applicant] / [respondent] [until [he] / [she] shall remarry] / [for so long as the order for periodical payments at paragraph [para number] below in the [applicant’s] / [respondent’s] favour shall subsist]; [and] / [or]
